Usage Terms for the JMA Game Servers. "JMA creative, JMA capturetheflag, JMA Voxelibre (Mineclone2)"

Status: 01.08.2025
Version: 1.3

    Scope of Application
    These Terms of Use apply to the use of the game servers "JMA creative, JMA capturetheflag, JMA Voxelibre (Mineclone2)" (hereinafter "Server"). By entering and using the server, the user fully accepts these terms. Users under 16 must have their legal guardians consent. If users do not agree to these conditions, they are prohibited from using the server.

    Rules and Conduct Guidelines
    a. Every user is obligated to adhere to the rules outlined below to ensure a friendly and respectful gaming environment:

    Offensive, insulting, or discriminatory content is strictly prohibited. This includes, but is not limited to: hate speech, threats, harassment, and obscenities.
    Users must report inappropriate content they encounter on the server immediately to the operator, either via the in-game reporting feature or through the provided contact information.
    Users have the right to defend themselves against inappropriate behavior of other players, but this should be done respectfully and non-confrontationally.
    Users must not intentionally damage the game or server environment or harm other users, e.g., through hacks, bots, or other unauthorized tools.
    Child safety: Any behavior endangering minors, such as sexual conduct or harassment towards underage users, will not be tolerated. Violations will result in immediate suspension, and relevant data will be forwarded to law enforcement authorities.
    Server rules must also be followed; these can be accessed with /rules.

    Playtime and Gaming Freedom
    The playtime on the server is generally unlimited. Users can access the server and participate in games at any time, provided they follow the rules. However, server management reserves the right to impose restrictions for maintenance, improvements, or other reasons specified herein.
    By moderation, bans or restrictions must not be circumvented. This includes mute, privileges removal, or exclusion from the server ("ban").

    Data Privacy
    a. The operator collects only the minimally necessary data to ensure smooth operation and security of the server, such as username, email address (if registration or activation is required), gameplay behavior, and technical info like IP addresses.
    b. All critical data collected will be protected to the best extent possible. The operator will implement appropriate security measures against unauthorized access and misuse.
    c. Data such as IP addresses may be shared with authorities in cases like:

    Suspicion of criminal acts such as cyberbullying, fraud, or other illegal activities observed on the server.
    Upon request from security authorities investigating user identity, usually within Germany and limited within the EU.
    Especially in cases of violations of child safety, requiring immediate reporting to law enforcement.
    Additional information on data privacy is available in the privacy policy.
    d. Data deletion requests can only be made via the email address below.

    Liability Disclaimer
    a. The operator assumes no liability for damages caused by using the server or due to insufficient server availability. This includes direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages.
    b. The content of linked pages is the responsibility of their respective providers or operators. Linked pages were checked for possible violations at the time of linking. Illegal content was not recognizable then. A permanent control of linked pages without concrete evidence of illegality is not reasonable.

    Changes to the Terms of Use
    The operator reserves the right to change these terms at any time. Changes will be announced within the server. It is the users’ responsibility to stay informed. Continued use of the server indicates acceptance of the updated terms.

    Whitelist Mode
    Some servers may operate in "Whitelist" mode, meaning only users on a specific list can join. Entries can only be made by admins, and requests for whitelist inclusion should be sent via email.

    Final Provisions
    a. If any provision of these terms becomes invalid, the remaining provisions remain unaffected. An effective regulation close to the invalid one will replace it, reflecting the original intent as closely as possible.

